The paper deals with information theoretic secure communication, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The problem involves eavesdropping, which is a common concern in network security (cs.NI) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses code construction and mapping, which are related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, and cs.DS, in that order.
